comments: Stewart (DET) legally contests Durant'S (BKN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Durant (BKN) makes contact with Stewart's (DET) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Joseph (DET) makes contact to Harden's (BKN) arm during his drive. The contact causes Harden to lose possession of the ball.
Griffin (BKN) makes contact with Stewart (DET) that impedes him in the post.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Harris (BKN), firms up and absorbs the contact.
Bey (DET) lowers his shoulder into Griffin's (BKN) body during his driving shot attempt and dislodges him from his position.
Stewart (DET) gives Durant (BKN) room to land on the jump shot attempt.
Stewart (DET) makes marginal contact with Durant's (BKN) body that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Joseph (DET) makes contact to Aldridge's (BKN) body and dislodges him from his position as he is receiving the pass.
Griffin (BKN) wraps Olynyk (DET) around the lower body in the post and affects his ability to get to the pass.
